			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">We've turned off the dyncode syscalls for PNaCl (issue 3109).  We also need to turn off NaCl's hardware exception handling feature for PNaCl.

The reasons are the same:
 * Reduce the attack surface.
 * Reduce access to non-portable features -- the exception handling interface returns non-portable register state.
